The paper deals with algorithms for computing tree and branch decompositions of graphs, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The focus is on k-outerplanar graphs, which are a subclass of planar graphs, and the paper provides bounds on the treewidth and branchwidth of these graphs. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are likely categories. Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial arguments and graph theory, which suggest categories such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
